<br>
The person who are being PL'ed will then single out each mob and hit them once each. Every mob except the last one will kill themselves on the druid, which will prolly be full health if mobs are &lt; lvl 30.<br>
<br>
I want the druid to take the hits since it will save a LOT of mana (A lvl 60 druid takes from 1-20 dam on most hits from mobs lvl 20-30, where as a lvl 15 char would take 50-60 dam). The person being PL'ed wont attract aggro in most pulls due to the little amount of damage he/she does to the mobs. <br>
<br>
My record is making a char from lvl 1-29 in 9 hours using this method.<br>
<br>
<br>
Once mobs reach lvl 40, DS dam is not enough to PL properly IMHO, and you need a melee to add some damage - which is why i find it hard to PL casters above lvl 40 unless they group with a melee.<br>
<br>
Magicians can help here. Pull a mob with debuff and let pet butcher the mob until the mob is almost dead. Reclaim pet and let PLchar-01 finish it off.<br>
I have not used this method since i find it difficult and troublesome to reclaim at the right time. <p>Baroness Majaharet<br />
